commit.message: Ignore empty strings as region_name and default to None to let boto3 decide which region to pick

Drop dead Pythons

CI is failing since boto won't work on some very old Python version.
Just outright drop these, since there's little point in supporting these
anyway.

Anyone needing to run on a system with an obsolete Python can use pyenv
and a virtualenv or something (they probably struggle with many other
tools anyway).

Use the configure region if one is set

awslogs isn't picking up the region if its set in the profile, since
passing ``region_name=None`` overrides this setting.
